node.title: Health authorities confirm Omicron COVID variant is in SA
node.alt: Hands wearing blue medical gloves handle 12 numbered vials.
node.description: Test results confirm two cases of COVID-19 recorded in South Australia are the Omicron variant.
node.content:
["Health authorities have confirmed two cases of COVID-19 recorded in South Australia\u00a0last week are the Omicron variant.\u00a0", "On Friday, SA Health revealed the two cases were\u00a0suspected to be the new Omicron variant based on the travellers' departure location.\u00a0", "Late last night, test results confirmed the suspicions.\u00a0", "No further Omicron cases have been reported in SA at this stage.", "Any close contacts of the Omicron cases have to quarantine for 14 days \u2014 regardless of their vaccination status \u2014 instead of the usual seven days.\u00a0", "There are four high-risk exposure sites linked to one or both of the cases:\u00a0", "In total, there are now more than 80 exposure sites across South Australia linked to positive COVID-19 cases.\u00a0", "The Den Restaurant at the Mayfair Hotel in the CBD on Monday, December 6 and an F45 gym at Glenelg East at several different times have been added to the list.\u00a0", "Yesterday SA recorded seven new cases of COVID 19, bringing the total number of active cases in the state to 54.", "Of the cases reported yesterday, five were vaccinated and two were unvaccinated.\u00a0", "Three COVID-19 patients remain in the Royal Adelaide Hospital in a stable condition.\u00a0", "", "
Why we hear about some COVID-19 variants more than others
"]
